I was going to respond to this thread yesterday, but ran out of time and I think Coinfist pretty much said everything that I was going to say.<br>
<br>
I'm honored to be flamed and praised in the same thread....well sorta:  Aego for sale on Gandor for 1500p, get em while supplies last.<br>
<br>
I always find it amusing when people send me tells saying they'll give me 1/2 the price I'm looking for saying I'll never get a better offer when 5 minutes later someone comes up and buys the spell for full price.  <br>
<br>
Who is missing out here?  Not me.  If you want the spell you'll pay for it.  If you think that mod1 is sufficient for your raiding needs, then stop seeking Mod3.  The spells that are priced high generally means that I'm not in a hurry to unload those spells.  I may even triple the normal going price just to hold on to the spell for guildies or future guildies.  If someone wants the spell bad enough, then they'll dish out the cash.<br>
<br>
You all think that once you hit level 55-56 you have a &quot;right&quot; to certain spells and want them dirt cheap, and that is just plain silly.  We're talking about spells that drop off mobs you probably won't be seeing for a month, maybe 2,3, or 4 and you want to be spoon-feed and handed your spells?  <br>
<br>
High demand spells will be priced accordingly.  If you don't have the plat, or your guild can't afford it, then chances are you're not ready for the spell.  This game has a certain progression.  If you were handed everything you wanted, this game would be crap because everyone would be running around with NToV, VT, etc loot killing dragons with an evil glare. <p>Macgee<br>
