<br>
If you want to talk to magicians, and be understood, then you should at least pay attention to the language they use. The numeric suffix &quot;2&quot; is already in use. Your attempt to use &quot;3&quot; is simply confusing, because magicians start to wonder if a third spell in the series has been recently added. If it had, that might help explain the price you are charging. However, you are simply making up your own name for an existing spell. &quot;When I use a word,&quot; Humpty Dumpty said, in rather a scornful tone, &quot;it means just what I choose it to mean—neither more nor less.&quot; My linguistics prof used that as an example of how not to communicate. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
