With that said I believe you deserve what you paid for through VI and they have it set up as a progression system.  Now when i tell you where you can get Mod3 (and that what im gonna call it because I and the rest of my guild refer to it as that as well as the three 60th mages in our guild) im only saying that it drops there and am not trying to be snide.  We have given away alot of spells for free, but they were spells that dropped commonly and were of no significant impact on the community progression wise but nice for the single players.  Example Nature Walkers Behest.  <br>
<br>
Like I said before we dont need the platinum.  We price the spells so only a small percent of the community will have the exclusive spell.  This is a goal of ours to keep the community as it is vs turn our server into a blue server over night.  <br>
<br>
We have reduced prices for other guilds who were unlucky with the mobs that drop the spell.  We have also given some very nice spells to a select few in other guilds who had spent significant time raiding with us.<br>
<br>
Mod3 will make your raid.  It will change what a mid level guild (now) cant do into something that guild can do with ease.  No more running out of mana, no more heavey mana/hp cost for your casters.  <br>
<br>
This spell if your guild cannot get it (raid wise) is what would be an investment. Try pooling money together or waiting for someone else to sell it or wait a while for the price to come down.  As more guilds progress and get closer to the mobs we will reduce the price until the point comes we dont sell it anymore. This is how I think working towards a healthy server without stiffling (sp) it respectability.<br>
<br>
Coinfist Heavyhand<br>
