<br>
Plain and simple.<br>
<br>
CotH is invaluable to gather you raid's people at a given spot, and add newcomers when you're already deep in a place, raising the chances yur raid will be successfull. You can very well stat to reach your target with minimal force and add the rest of needed people as they arrive.<br>
<br>
RoMT... if you've never had one in your hands, you can't understand how usefull it is. Invaluable to speed up buffing, like when your clerics have to toss a few blessings of aegolism, or shammies on group focus, or enchanters on KEI... Try buffing a raid force with and without RoMT, and compare the time. Not to mention, once you have everyone ready, you will continue supplying mana to nukers and healers, making it possible to acomplish thing you couldn't dream of doing without.<br>
<br>
